{
  "stem": "12462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I said, I don't want to do any more of this without taking some parachuting myself.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I went down to Fort Benning in May of 1944 and took a four-week course of parachuting and then came back.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that actually led to another transfer to other kinds of work.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "May and June.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The invasion of-- the Allied invasion on June 6, 1944 took place while I happened to be in Fort Benning taking parachute training.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was head of what was called the German Labor Branch of the Office of Strategic Services.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, he didn't speak German himself, but he was a-- had a-- a great ability.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was obviously shown by a lot of things he did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he'd been an attorney to labor unions, and so he had a sympathy for dealing with people who would be in opposition to the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I got back to Washington, I was walking down the street with my parachute wings on, and I ran into a man by the name of Jack Oley, who was an administrative assistant to Colonel William Brennan, who later became a Supreme Court Justice.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, Jack Oley had been a-- a year ahead of me at Harvard Law School.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when he saw me on the street with these parachute bars and a bunch of stripes on my arm that I'd been overseas he says, I think we need you to help get manpower moved from the South up to the North, with the factories that are needed, to settle strikes and so on.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we got a branch in the Army called the Labor Branch, the Army Service Forces, and I want you there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said, you'll never get me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I've just come out of parachute school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He said, we'll see.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
